dbs.name: Oracle
dbs.about: Oracle Autonomous Database is an all-in-one cloud database solution for data marts, data lakes, operational reporting, and batch data processing.

dbs.name: Oracle Cloud
dbs.about: Oracle Autonomous Database is an all-in-one cloud database solution for data marts, data lakes, operational reporting, and batch data processing.

dbs.name: MySQL Cloud
dbs.about: MySQL is an Oracle-backed open source relational database management system (RDBMS) very popular with web applications and online publishing.

dbs.name: MySQL
dbs.about: MySQL is an Oracle-backed open source relational database management system (RDBMS) very popular with web applications and online publishing.

dbs.name: Microsoft SQL Server
dbs.about: Microsoft SQL Server is a industry standard relational database management system (RDBMS) used in a wide variety of BI and analytics applications.

dbs.name: PostgreSQL
dbs.about: PostgreSQL also known as Postgres, is a free and open-source relational database management system (RDBMS) emphasizing extensibility and SQL compliance.

dbs.name: MongoDB
dbs.about: MongoDB is a cross-platform document-oriented and NoSQL database.

dbs.name: Snowflake
dbs.about: The Snowflake Cloud Data Platform includes a pure cloud, SQL data warehouse.

dbs.name: Elasticsearch
dbs.about: Elasticsearch is the world’s leading free and open search and analytics solution with an emphasis on speed and scalability.

dbs.name: Db2
dbs.about: Db2, or Database 2, is a set of relational database products built and offered by IBM to store, analyze and retrieve data with maximum performance.

dbs.name: IBM Db2 z/OS
dbs.about: IBM Db2 for z/OS is a relational database management system that runs on the mainframe.

dbs.name: IBM Db2 Cloud
dbs.about: IBM Db2 on Cloud is a fully managed SQL cloud database with point-in-time recovery and high-availability disaster recovery (HADR).

dbs.name: IBM Db2 iSeries
dbs.about: IBM Db2 is a family of data management products, including the Db2 relational database.

dbs.name: SQLite
dbs.about: SQLite implements a small, fast, self-contained, high-reliability, full-featured, SQL database engine.

dbs.name: Microsoft Access
dbs.about: Microsoft Access is a database management system (DBMS) from Microsoft that combines the relational Access Database Engine (ACE) with a graphical user interface and software-development tools.

dbs.name: Cassandra
dbs.about: Apache Cassandra is an open source NoSQL distributed database trusted by thousands of companies for scalability and high availability.

dbs.name: MariaDB
dbs.about: MariaDB is an open source relational database management system (DBMS) that is a compatible drop-in replacement for the widely used MySQL.

dbs.name: Databricks
dbs.about: Databricks is a unified data analytics platform that provides a collaborative environment for data engineering, data science, and machine learning at scale.

dbs.name: Azure SQL Database
dbs.about: Azure SQL Database is a SQL Server database engine, based on the latest stable Enterprise Edition of SQL Server and fully managed by Azure.

dbs.name: Google BigQuery
dbs.about: BigQuery is a fully-managed, serverless data warehouse that enables scalable analysis over petabytes of data. It is a Platform as a Service (PaaS) that supports querying using ANSI SQL.

dbs.name: Hive
dbs.about: Apache Hive is a distributed, fault-tolerant data warehouse system that enables analytics at a massive scale.

dbs.name: Teradata
dbs.about: Teradata is a Relational Database Management System (RDBMS) suitable for large data warehousing applications.

dbs.name: Solr
dbs.about: Solr is a fast, open source enterprise search platform built on Apache Lucene™.

dbs.name: SAP ASE
dbs.about: SAP ASE is a relational model database server developed by Sybase Corporation.

dbs.name: Firebird
dbs.about: Firebird is an open-source SQL relational database management system that runs on Linux, Microsoft Windows, macOS and several Unix platforms.

dbs.name: Azure Synapse Serverless
dbs.about: Azure Synapse Serverless offers flexible and cost-effective data processing without the need to manage infrastructure, enabling rapid and scalable data analytics.

dbs.name: Azure Synapse Dedicated
dbs.about: Azure Synapse Dedicated is a powerful and scalable data platform providing high performance and reliability for data warehousing and analytics solutions.

dbs.name: Informix
dbs.about: IBM Informix is an embeddable, high-performance database for integrating SQL, NoSQL, JSON, time-series and spatial data that's designed for analytics int the cloud.

dbs.name: ClickHouse
dbs.about: ClickHouse is a fast open-source column-oriented database management system that allows generating analytical data reports in real-time using SQL queries.

dbs.name: Redshift
dbs.about: Redshift is a data warehouse product which forms part of the larger cloud-computing platform Amazon Web Services.

dbs.name: Vertica
dbs.about: Vertica is a columnar data storage platform designed to handle large volumes of data, which enables very fast query performance in traditionally intensive scenarios.

dbs.name: Presto
dbs.about: Presto is a distributed query engine for big data using the SQL query language.

dbs.name: Greenplum
dbs.about: Greenplum Database GPDB is an advanced, fully featured, open source data warehouse, based on PostgreSQL.

dbs.name: Netezza
dbs.about: IBM Netezza is a powerful and highly parallelized Data Warehousing system that is simple to administer and to maintain.

dbs.name: H2
dbs.about: H2 is a open source rdbms that can be embedded in Java applications or run in client-server mode.

dbs.name: Trino
dbs.about: Trino is an ANSI SQL compliant query engine, that works with a wide variety of BI tools.

dbs.name: Derby
dbs.about: Apache Derby is a rdbms developed by the Apache Software Foundation focusing on easy installation and usage with a minimal disk-space footprint.

dbs.name: SingleStore
dbs.about: SingleStore (formerly MemSQL) is a cloud-native database designed for data-intensive applications. A distributed, relational, SQL database management system (RDBMS) that features ANSI SQL support.

dbs.name: Actian X (Ingres)
dbs.about: Actian X is a combination of Ingres transactional and Vector analytic databases, integration and a monitoring tool.

dbs.name: SAP SQL Anywhere (Sybase SQL Anywhere)
dbs.about: SAP SQL Anywhere is a proprietary relational database management system (RDBMS) product from SAP.

dbs.name: Progress
dbs.about: Progress OpenEdge RDBMS supports modern, mission-critical, business applications developed using the OpenEdge application development platform

dbs.name: HSQLDB
dbs.about: HSQLDB (HyperSQL DataBase) is a SQL relational database system written in Java. It offers a small, fast multithreaded and transactional database.

dbs.name: InterSystems IRIS
dbs.about: Iris is an object-oriented database management system being developed at Hewlett-Packard Laboratories.

dbs.name: DataDirect's Autonomous REST Connector
dbs.about: Progress DataDirect Autonomous REST Connector is an intelligent, customizable data connectivity solution enabling build and deploy of data connectors without coding.

dbs.name: Salesforce.com
dbs.about: The Salesforce Database is powered by Oracle. There are a number of languages that are used for the Salesforce Database including SQL.

dbs.name: CData Software JDBC Drivers
dbs.about: Easy-to-use JDBC Drivers with powerful Enterprise-level features. Connect JDBC with Salesforce, NetSuite, SharePoint, Secure File Transfer, and more.

dbs.name: SAP IQ (Sybase IQ)
dbs.about: SAP IQ is a column-based, petabyte scale, relational database software system used for BI, data warehousing, and data marts. Replaced by Yellowbrick.

dbs.name: MaxDB
dbs.about: MaxDB is a heavy-duty, SAP-certified open source database that offers high availability, scalability and a comprehensive feature set.

dbs.name: Exasol
dbs.about: Exasol is a high-performance, in-memory, MPP database specifically designed for analytics of large data sets in real time.

dbs.name: IBM IMS
dbs.about: IBM IMS is a hierarchical database management software system for online transaction processing (OLTP) and online batch processing.

dbs.name: HPE NonStop SQL
dbs.about: NonStop SQL is a relational database management system designed for fault tolerance and scalability, offered by HP.

dbs.name: NuoDB
dbs.about: NuoDB is an SQL-oriented transactional database management system (DBMS) designed for distributed deployment in the cloud.

dbs.name: Yellowbrick
dbs.about: Yellowbrick Data Warehouse is an advanced, massively parallel processing (MPP) SQL database designed for batch, real-time, ad hoc, and mixed workloads.

dbs.name: CrateDB
dbs.about: CrateDB is a open-source distributed SQL database management system that integrates a fully searchable document-oriented data store.

dbs.name: FrontBase
dbs.about: FrontBase is a relational database management system written in ANSI C to be scalable and fast.

dbs.name: Mimer SQL
dbs.about: Mimer SQL is a high performance database engine, targeted at mission-critical client/server environments while offering scaleable performance on multiple plattforms.
